The paper deals with algorithms for graph partitioning and cut-improvement, which are topics in the field of data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of flow computations and conductance measures also suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The mention of "learning applications" in the abstract further supports the possibility of the paper falling under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
